==English==

===Etymology===
[[Greek]] {{italbrac|kryptos}} + [[Latin]] ''-[[ides]].'' (Eng. usg. 1983; coined by John E. Wall in the ''ISC Newsletter'')

===Nouns===
{{en-noun}}

# {{italbrac|cryptozoology}} Any [[creature]] that may or may not exist. Cryptids are hypothetical creatures that have been “sighted” or [[seen]], but are not proven real. Anything can be mistaken for these creatures. For example, a bear can be mistaken for [[Bigfoot]].

